                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_aslam" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>aslam</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>aslan</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>дешевый</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>cheap</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>дешево</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>cheaply</q></tr></sense></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>aslam fydy bas næj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>дешевое мясо не дает навара</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>cheap meat does not give fat</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 192</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>aslam fydy bas næj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>дешевое мясо не дает навара</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>cheap meat does not give fat</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 192</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из %bсев.тюрк.%b (казан., тобольск., крым., барабин.) aslam ‘выгода’, ‘барыш’, aslamnu ‘выгодный’; отсюда и <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><lang/> <w>ослам</w> <gloss><q>барыш</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><w>слам</w> <gloss><q>барыш</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><w/> <gloss><q>добыча</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ВЯ"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1958 I 120 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1958 I 120 ff.</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><lang/> <w>асламщик, осламщик</w> <gloss><q>перекупщик</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. также <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>alsam</w> <gloss><q>вдоволь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ce"><w/> <gloss><q>вполне</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><w/> <gloss><q>более</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><w>alsam dar</w> <gloss><q>прибавлять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><w/> <gloss><q>прибавление</q></gloss></mentioned>, ; развитие значения: ‘выгодный’ → ‘дешевый’. Для ‘барыша’ осетинский имеет другое, тоже заимствованное слово <ref type="xr" target="#entry_paida"/>. О терминах торговли см. под словом <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arǧ"/> ‘цена’.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From %bNorth Turkic%b (Kazan, Tobol, Krym, Barabin) %iaslam%i ‘benefit’, ‘profit’, %iaslamnu%i ‘profitable’; derived from it is <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><lang/> <w>ослам</w> <gloss><q>profit</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><w>слам</w> <gloss><q>benefit</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><w/> <gloss><q>plunder</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ВЯ"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1958 I 120 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1958 I 120 ff.</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="ru-x-dial"><lang/> <w>асламщик, осламщик</w> <gloss><q>reseller</q></gloss></mentioned>; consider also <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>alsam</w> <gloss><q>plenty</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ce"><w/> <gloss><q>quite</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><w/> <gloss><q>more</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><w>alsam dar</w> <gloss><q>add</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><w/> <gloss><q>addition</q></gloss></mentioned>, ; the meaning shift is ‘profitable’ → cheap ’. For ‘profit’ Ossetic has another, also borrowed word <ref type="xr" target="#entry_paida"/>. For trading terms, see the word <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arǧ"/> ‘price’.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>